Name: Träram
Short description: En tidlös och elegant träram som kompletterar dina konstverk perfekt. Tillverkad av högkvalitativt trä i en enkel och klassisk design. Den naturliga trästrukturen ger en varm och inbjudande känsla till dina tavlor. Med sina måtten 50 x 76 cm är den idealisk för att rama in dina favoritkonstverk och göra dem till centrum för ditt rum. Enkelheten i designen gör att konsten får ta centrum i uppmärksamheten.

Name: Hilma af Klint poster
Description: Hilma af Klint, en pionjär inom abstrakt konst, är känd för sina färgstarka och geometriska målningar. Hennes verk utforskar komplexa mönster, symboler och abstrakta former som utmanar konventionella konstnärliga normer. Genom sina färgrika kompositioner väckte hon nyfikenhet och föregick sin tid, och hennes arv lever vidare som en inspirationskälla för modern konst.

Name: Ailie Banks prints
Description: Based in Australia Ailie is a bisexual illustrator, activist, content creator & community worker. Ailie's pronouns are She/Her, and she lives openly with ADHD & Complex trauma. Advocacy is integral to her art practise & community work with particular focus on gender equity & mental health. Ailie has spent the last 5+ years building her career as an artist, a Violence prevention worker, the Author of 'The Book of Bitch', a semi-popular instagrammer, in addition to illustrating for global brands, individuals & Not-for-profits alike.

Name: gggrimes posters
Description:

Theodoor Grimes is a Black digital artist known for his vibrant illustrations that center the queer experience under the moniker ggggrimes (pronounced Grimes). Based in the Bronx, NY, Theodoor is entirely self taught. Their art career started in 2018, when after a year of vigorous self study with ink and watercolors during their final year in music school, Theodoor decided they wanted to dedicate their life to visual artwork. Although his family was homeless and had been for many years, he was supported in his goals. On his birthday on April 22nd, 2018, he was gifted his first drawing tablet, opening up new doors to creative expression.
